Upon reaching the washing well, he settled against the stone structure.  &quot;Go ahead and wash up.&quot;  He nodded towards the water. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#993300>(6/5/03 7:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.speedis.org/images/214.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Apology</span><hr size=1> Kalasin nodded somewhat solemnly, certainly not the jovial person that she had been prior to this incident. It had confirmed everything that deep down she already knew. No matter where she went, who she was with… she would always be the same person, the same violent killer when push came to shove.<br>
The amazon woman pulled a bucket of water out of the well and quickly poured the clear liquid out over her weapon. She put it back in it's place after it was clean and then looked back up to Theseus.<br>
<br>
&quot;I didn't mean it.&quot; she said quietly. &quot;I tried to tell him…&quot;<br>
<br>
The amazon was used to pleading her case with people, and it showed. However, after a moment, she seemed to compose her somewhat sad look and smile smally.<br>
